<br>
And yes raid leaders do ask around on people they don't know.  I do this.  If I see someone sign up that is a class I need I ask my friends (especially if they are in that person's guild) what they are like.  Its really risky taking someone that you have no clue who they are....they could be Deamonwolf or Beliael /shudder.<br>
<br>
Best thing to do is just watch the boards and see what raids you can get into, not planar, but any.  Many guilds that hold smaller raids like Chardok, CoM, Kedge, etc at times tend to have a lack of good enchanters.  Stepping up and helping them will make a good impression and get you in future raids.  Too bad you work on Sundays as I have a Hate raid Sunday the 4th and could probably squeeze you in. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukruuunch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kruuunch</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ugliest Paladin o' Kaladim</span><br>  Posts: 1333<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/26/01 10:54:35 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.krunch.net/kruunch-face.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The basic: How do I get on planes raids?</span><hr size=1> Giving the raid leader 20K in plats and a Fungi Tunic doesn't hurt either. <p><FONT face="arial" size="-1"><B>Kruunch Spiritslammer (Ugliest Paladin o' Kaladim)
